'''''How It Should Have Ended''''' ('''HISHE''') is an [[Animation|animated]] webseries that parodies popular films by creating alternate endings and pointing out various flaws. Endings for many major movies have been presented, using the tagline ‘sometimes movies don't finish the way we'd like’.

== History ==

''How It Should Have Ended'' began after Daniel Baxter and Tommy Watson started discussing alternate endings for a movie they had watched. In 2005 their first animation ''How Matrix Revolutions Should Have Ended'' was completed and soon after in July 2005 the website was established.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.howitshouldhaveended.com/about-hishe|title = About How It Should Have Ended|date = |accessdate = October 30, 2015|website = www.howitshouldhaveended.com|publisher = |last = |first = |deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130724055833/http://www.howitshouldhaveended.com/about-hishe|archivedate = July 24, 2013|df = }}</ref> Christina "Tina" Alexander,<ref>{{cite web|title = Howitshouldhaveended.com Whois Lookup - Who.is - Who.is|url = http://who.is/whois/www.howitshouldhaveended.com|website = who.is|accessdate = 2015-10-31}}</ref> who has previously worked with Daniel, joined the team shortly thereafter.

''HISHE'' was awarded the "Best Internet Parody" award for ''How Superman Should Have Ended'' by Spike TV at the 2006 [[Scream Awards]] at the [[Pantages Theatre (Hollywood)|Pantages Theater]] Hollywood, California.<ref>[http://www.geeksofdoom.com/2006/10/09/spike-tvs-scream-awards-winners "Spike TV's Scream Awards Winners!"] ''Geeks of Doom'', 6 October 2006.</ref> and was featured in an MTV Comedy and Talent Showcase at the Hollywood Improv.  It has also been featured as a Yahoo! Profile Pick and has appeared in both ''Fade In'' and ''Wired'' magazines.<ref>Watercutter, Angela. [https://www.wired.com/underwire/2011/08/video-harry-potter-alternate-ending-uses-magic-duh/ Video: Harry Potter Alternate Ending Uses ‘Magic, Duh’]. ''Wired'', 18 August 2011.</ref>

On March 5, 2007 HISHE was launched on [[YouTube]] as HISHEdotcom. It has attracted notable appearances such as [[Stan Lee]] himself in the parody of ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film)|The Amazing Spider-Man]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.howitshouldhaveended.com/forum/amazing-spider-man|title = Forum-Amazing Spider Man|date = |accessdate = October 30, 2015|website = www.howitshouldhaveended.com|publisher = |last = |first = |deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130724055826/http://www.howitshouldhaveended.com/forum/amazing-spider-man|archivedate = July 24, 2013|df = }}</ref>

In September 2009 ''How It Should Have Ended'' joined Starz Digital Media which now handles all licensing. In April 2010, How It Should Have Ended was awarded the [[2nd Streamy Awards|Streamy Award]] for Best Animated Web Series at the Orpheum Theatre in Los Angeles.<ref>[http://blip.tv/streamys/how-it-should-have-ended-best-animated-web-series-2010-streamy-awards-5572377 How It Should Have Ended - Best Animated Web Series - 2010 Streamy Awards] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929142853/http://blip.tv/streamys/how-it-should-have-ended-best-animated-web-series-2010-streamy-awards-5572377 |date=2013-09-29 }}. ''Blip TV''. Retrieved October 30, 2015</ref><ref>{{cite web|title = Superman wins awards at Spike TV SCREAM AWARDS [Archive]  - The SuperHeroHype Forums|url = http://forums.superherohype.com/archive/index.php/t-252596.html|website = forums.superherohype.com|accessdate = 2015-10-31}}</ref>

On June 30, 2013, a video was uploaded on [[TheFineBros]] channel which features the Teens React teens watching the ''Lord of the Rings'', ''Harry Potter'', and ''The Hunger Games'' HISHE Videos.

In November 2013, Batman and Superman from "Super Cafe" guest starred in the [[Nostalgia Critic]]'s review of [[Man of Steel (film)|''Man of Steel'']], at the end of the episode where The Critic parodies Super Cafe. ''HISHE'' also featured in the [[Screen Junkies]] series Honest Trailers in the episodes about ''[[The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies]]'' and ''[[Star Trek Into Darkness]]''.

=== Statistics ===

As of April 6, 2014, HISHE had '''3,328,232''' subscribers and '''673,522,879''' views.<ref name="youtube1">{{cite web|title = How It Should Have Ended|url = https://www.youtube.com/user/HISHEdotcom|website = YouTube|accessdate = 2015-10-31}}</ref> As of January 10, 2015, about 8 months later, HISHE had '''4,418,182''' subscribers and '''879,357,066''' views. A further 16 months later (May 18, 2016), HISHE had '''6,140,916''' subscribers and '''1,365,102,166''' views. Currently HISHE has more than 7.7 million subcribers in the year of 2018.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/user/HISHEdotcom/about?&ab_channel=HowItShouldHaveEnded [accessed on: 18 May 2016]</ref> By the same time, HISHE had amassed over '''200,000''' likes on its Facebook account,<ref>https://www.facebook.com/howitshouldhaveended/ [accessed on: 18 May 2016]</ref> over '''19,000''' followers on its Instagram account<ref>https://www.instagram.com/hishegram/ [accessed on: 18 May 2016]</ref> and over '''11,000''' followers on its Twitter account.<ref>https://twitter.com/thehishedotcom?lang=en-gb [accessed on: 18 May 2016]</ref>

=== Critical reception ===

HISHE has received many positive reviews<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2061165/|title = How It Should Have Ended on Internet Movie Data Base|date = |accessdate = October 30, 2015|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mrmovie-review.com/tag/how-it-should-have-ended/ "FUN STUFF: How Iron Man 3 should have ended"]. ''MidRoad Review'', 30 May 2013</ref><ref>Jones, Zach. [http://www.tubefilter.com/2008/02/01/review-of-how-it-should-have-ended/ "Review of How it Should Have Ended"]. ''Tubefilter'', 01 February 2008.</ref><ref>[http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/reviews.php?target_group=&target_title=WebAnimation%2FHowItShouldHaveEnded "Web Animation/How It Should Have Ended"].''TV Tropes'', 27 December 2012.</ref> about its animation and alternate endings to popular movies. [[IMDb]] gave it a rating of 8.3/10 from 2,484 users.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2061165/|title = How It Should Have Ended (2005-)|date = |accessdate = October 30, 2015|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Some of the parodies which were most popular with the reviewers are of ''[[Lord of the Rings (film series)|Lord of the Rings]]'', ''[[Spider-Man 3]]'', ''[[Harry Potter (film series)|Harry Potter]]'' and ''[[Superman (1978 film)|Superman]]''.<ref>[http://www.filmschoolrejects.com/news/how-man-of-steel-should-have-ended.php "How ‘Man of Steel’ Should Have Ended"]. ''Film School Rejects:Movie News''. 21 July 2013.</ref>  HISHE's short animations of [[Superman]] and [[Batman]] sitting in a café (dubbed Super Cafe), discussing various flaws in movies along with the characters of the movie such as ''[[Iron Man (2008 film)|Iron Man]]'', ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' and even the ''[[Super Mario]]'' games, have also been well received.

